CHANGELOG.md:5:- Added depth-2 production course helpers (frac-0014): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/production_course.py` now exposes frozen `CourseSummary`, `ChapterDigest`, `ArcPhaseSnapshot`, and `CourseArcPlan` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_course`, `chapter_digest`, `catalog_digest`, `arc_phase_snapshot`, `arc_phase_snapshots`, `course_titles`, `plan_course_arc`, and `validate_course` so runtime diagnostics and tests can render an operator-readable view of a section course (chapter count, transition type, mix role, resolved concept titles in declared chapter order), digest each chapter with its first three sample concept values, snapshot every required arc phase with a `sparse` / `balanced` / `dense` density bucket, plan an arc end-to-end by reusing `course_for_section` across a sequence of section descriptors with the last transition cleanly resolving to `terminal`, and report unknown-value chapters as a sorted tuple. Existing `REQUIRED_CHAPTER_IDS`, `REQUIRED_PHASE_NAMES`, `COURSE_CHAPTERS`, `ARC_PHASE_PROFILES`, `load_course_chapters`, `load_arc_phase_profiles`, `course_chapter`, `course_concept`, `arc_phase_profile`, `transition_type_for_section`, and `course_for_section` semantics are preserved so the score-tree composer and `tests/test_production_course_knowledge_base.py` / `tests/test_production_course_integration.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_production_course_depth.py` pins summary title order, chapter digest metadata + `KeyError` on unknown ids, catalog digest coverage, density bucketing + `KeyError` on unknown phase, end-to-end arc plan + empty short-circuit, and validator behavior, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:7:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:9:- Added depth-2 genre literacy helpers (frac-0012): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/genre_literacy.py` now exposes frozen `GenreSummary` / `GenreBlend` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_strategy`, `genre_compatibility`, `blend_genre_strategies`, and `recommend_genre_sequence` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can render a stable per-genre summary (label, tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, voice count, dominant grooves, top arc phases, calm/balanced/intense mood bucket), score a bounded `[0.0, 1.0]` symmetric compatibility between two traditions from arc-affinity cosine, modal/groove Jaccard ratios, and texture/chromatic distance, blend numeric hints with a clamped `[0.0, 1.0]` weight (tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, rubato tolerance, repetition tolerance, spatial width, sorted shared modal preferences), and plan one genre per supplied arc phase with rolling fatigue from prior selections. Existing `GenreStrategy`/`REQUIRED_GENRES` data, `strategy_for_genre`, `all_strategies`, `genre_arc_affinity`, `best_genres_for_phase`, and `select_genre` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_genre_literacy_depth.py` pins summary stability and mood bucketing, compatibility self-identity / symmetry / boundedness with related-vs-contrasted ranking, blend interpolation / clamp / modal intersection, sequence per-phase coverage with no immediate repeats, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:11:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:13:- Added depth-2 generation client_protocol helpers (frac-0010): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` now exposes a frozen `GenerationOutcome` dataclass plus pure helpers `cost_per_second`, `result_summary`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` so any backend (Replicate, Modal, local Ada, fakes) can compute USD-per-second cost from a `GenerationResult`, render a stable operator-readable summary dict (rounded duration / cost / per-second cost), emit a single-line `model=… dur=…s cost=$… latency=…ms id=…` log entry with `<unknown>` substituted for an empty `api_request_id`, and validate a result against its `GenerationRequest` (model match, sample-rate floor, duration tolerance, non-negative cost, non-negative latency) into a typed pass/fail outcome with stable reason ordering. The existing `GenerationResult` field order, `GenerationClient` Protocol contract, and downstream `client_replicate` / `client_modal` / `client_local` paths are preserved; `tests/test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins outcome shape, zero-duration cost handling, summary rounding, log-line ID fallback, and accumulated validation reasons, while existing client protocol, Replicate retry, Modal, local-Ada, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:15:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:17:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
